n respect to their morality, humanity, honesty, character and health. These activities also contribute to the development of soft skills or employable skills to great extent, which are ultimately required at the world of work.<br>\r\n\r\nCurrent year Academic Calendar: Click Here<br>\r\nCurrent year Time Table: Term-211<br>\r\nCo-curricular Activities: Click Here<br>\r\nDepartment Curriculum Booklet: Click Here <br>\r\nDepartment Information Booklet: Click Here<br>\r\nMID Sem Exam Time Table and Result: Term-211<br>\r\nE-Newsletter of the Department: Jan-June2021<br>\r\n\r\n<b>CONTACT US</b><br>\r\n\r\nMechanical Engineering Department<br>\r\n\r\nDr. S. & S.S Ghandhy College of Engineering and Technology, Majura Gate, Surat<br>\r\n\r\nInstitute E mail: ssgp-surat-dte@ gujarat.gov.in      Contact No. 0261-2655799<br>\r\n\r\nDepartment E mail: mechdeptssg@gmail.com<br>\" ', '0000-00-00'),
(21, 'METALLURGY ENGG', ' In 1965, Metallurgy Department was established in Dr. S. & S. S. Ghandhy College of Engineering and Technology, Surat, South Gujarat. This is the only institute that offers diploma metallurgy program in Gujarat. Institute is governed by Department of Technical Education, Government of Gujarat. Diploma metallurgy program is approved by All India council for technical education (AICTE), New Delhi and is affiliated to Gujarat Technological University, Ahmedabad.<br><br>\r\n\r\nMetallurgy department strives hard in order to fulfil the growing global demands of skilled human resource in the field of metals. Metallurgy deals with production, properties, uses, shaping and treating of metals and their alloys. All the faculties of the department are well educated and most of the faculties have registered for Ph.D. Since the inception of the department, its alumni are well placed in various industries and academics.<br><br>\r\n\r\nAccreditation Status: Click Here<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>STUDENT INTAKE/YEAR:</b><br>\r\n\r\nName of Department      Year   Student Intake<br>\r\nMetallurgy Department  1965   30<br>\r\nMetallurgy Department  2004   62<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>DURATION OF COURSE:</b><br>\r\n03 years, six semesters. Students are offered full time industrial training in 6th semester as a part of curriculum.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>ENTRY LEVEL:</b><br>\r\n\r\n1. 10th Standard Pass (1st Sem. Entry)<br>\r\n\r\n2. Certificate course of duration 2 years from ITI (3rd Sem. Entry)<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>ADMISSION:</b><br>\r\n\r\nAdmission through Central Admission Committee for Professional Diploma Courses on the basis of state level merit List. For More information visit www.acpdc.co.in<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>VISION:</b><br>\r\n\r\n“To lead in diploma metallurgical engineering education with focus on innovation and sustainable development of industry and society”.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>MISSION:</b><br>\r\n\r\nTo impart and empower students with relevant knowledge, competence and creativity with special emphasis on metallurgical engineering.<br>\r\nTo promote conducive environment for all round development of students.<br>\r\nTo promote linkages with external agencies to meet changing needs of industry and society.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>PROGRAM EDUCATIONAL OBJECTIVES (PEOs):</b><br>\r\nThe metallurgy diploma graduate will be able to make successful career in metallurgical industry to meet ever changing needs of industry.<br>\r\nTo enable diploma graduate for lifelong learning and higher studies.<br>\r\nIdentifying and engage in innovation, become an entrepreneur for sustainable development of society.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>PROGRAM SPECIFIC OUTCOMES (PSOs):</b><br>\r\nApply the fundamental knowledge of metallurgy for the benefit of society, industries and research organizations.<br>\r\nDiploma holders will be able to select suitable techniques for testing of metals and alloys.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>PROGRAM OUTCOMES (POs):</b><br>\r\nBasic and Discipline specific knowledge: Apply knowledge of basic mathematics, science and engineering fundamentals and engineering specialization to solve the engineering problems.<br>\r\nProblem analysis: Identify and analyze well-defined engineering problems using codified standard methods.<br>\r\nDesign/ development of solutions: Design solutions for well-defined technical problems and assist with the design of systems components or processes to meet specified needs.<br>\r\nEngineering Tools, Experimentation and Testing: Apply modern engineering tools and appropriate technique to conduct standard tests and measurements.<br>\r\nEngineering practices for society, sustainability and environment: Apply appropriate technology in context of society, sustainability, environment and ethical practices.<br>\r\nProject Management: Use engineering management principles individually, as a team member or a leader to manage projects and effectively communicate about well-defined engineering activities.<br>\r\nLife-long learning: Ability to analyze individual needs and engage in updating in the context of technological changes.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>TRAINING & PLACEMENT OPPORTUNITIES:</b><br>\r\nEvery year all the students of semester 6 are placed for full term (14 weeks) industrial training as a part of curriculum.<br>\r\n\r\nList of industry where students undergone Industrial training in Academic Year: 2017  2018  2019  2020<br>\r\n\r\nEvery year campus drives are held at Institute by various metallurgical companies. Many students are placed through on/off campus drive. Most of the pass outs either get placement or go for further studies. <br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>List of industries/companies hired our graduates in past few years is given below.</b><br>\r\nArcelor Mittal Nippon Steel India Ltd, Hazira<br>\r\nLarsen & Toubro Ltd, Surat<br>\r\nHindalco Industries Ltd (Birla copper), Bharuch<br>\r\nUttamgalva, Vardha<br>\r\nTheis Precision India Pvt Ltd, Navsari<br>\r\nSchaeffler India Limited, Vadodara<br>\r\nRoyal Arc Electrodes Ltd., Bhilad<br>\r\nMiranda Tools, Ankleshwar<br>\r\nChina Steel Corporation India Pvt. Ltd., Bharuch<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>CO-CURRICULAR & EXTRA CURRICULAR ACTIVITIES</b><br>\r\n\r\nEven though, knowledge and academics are important for every student, it is necessary to develop skills and talents through extra-Curricular and Co-Curricular Activities, for the overall personality development of student. Activities like Food Festival, Important Day Celebration, Tree plantation, Cleanliness drive, Yoga celebrations, Sports week, Group Discussions, Mock Interview, Finishing School, NCC and NSS activities are planned and organised in department and institute level for an overall development of students. In every term expert lectures, seminar/workshop/webinar and industrial visits are arranged by metallurgy department. For first year students Thalassemia Test is conducted at institute level. Every year institute is organizing blood donation camp students and faculty supports and contributes in it. <br><br>\r\n\r\nCurrent year Academic Calendar: Term-211<br>\r\nCurrent year Time Table: Term-211<br>\r\nDepartment Information Booklet: Click Here<br>\r\nDepartment E-Newsletter: 2018   2019   2020<br>\r\nMID Sem Exam Result: Sem-5<br>\r\nDepartmental Co-Curricular & Extra Curricular Activities: 2017-18  2018-19  2019-20<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>CONTACT US</b><br>\r\n\r\nMetallurgy Department,<br>\r\n\r\nDr. S. & S.S Ghandhy College of Engineering and Technology,<br>\r\n\r\nMajura Gate, Surat<br>\r\n\r\nInstitute E mail: ssgp-surat-dte@ gujarat.gov.in     <br>\r\n\r\nContact No. 0261-2655799<br>\r\n\r\nDepartment E mail: metssg21@gmail.com <br>\" ', '0000-00-00'),
(24, 'POWER ELECTRONICS', ' Since 1984, Government of Gujarat has offered 03 Year Power electronics course for the undergraduate students with an intake of 20 seats. Being multidisciplinary branch no of intake were increased from 20 to 30 and 30 to 60 from 1990 to 2001 respectively. Department has established various laboratories like power electronics lab, basic electronics lab, instrumentation lab, computer lab, project lab etc along with modern instruments for the laboratory experiments in the emerging world of power electronics and research work. Department offered six months industrial training program along with project to final year students in various industries like ESSAR, KRIBHCO, NTPC, RELIANCE, L & T,HIREL, INDUCTOTHERM, ELECTROTHERM etc. Department has well qualified and experienced staff having M.E./M.Tech degree.<br><br>\r\n\r\nTo produce quality technocrats in the field of power electronics to contribute industries as well as future power sector and quality of power for the nation growth at large while maintaining professional ethics for the benefit of society.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>VISION</b><br>\r\n\r\n“To be a unique center of excellence in power electronics technical education innovation for sustainable growth of industry and society.\"<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>MISSION</b><br>\r\n\r\n1. To impart viable technical core competence in Power Electronics.<br>\r\n\r\n2. To respond effectively to the needs of Power Electronics industry and community at large.<br>\r\n\r\n3. To promote faculty members to excel and in turn motivate the students to achieve excellence in Power Electronics.<br>\r\n\r\n4. To develop conducive campus environment for qualitative learning and innovation.<br>\r\n\r\n5. To inculcate moral, ethical and professional values amongst the students.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Program Educational Outcomes (PEOs)</b><br>\r\n\r\nPEO-1: Provide socially responsible, environment friendly solutions to Power Electronics related problems adapting professional ethics.<br>\r\n\r\nPEO-2: Adapt state-of-the-art Power Electronics technologies to work in multi-disciplinary work environments.<br>\r\n\r\nPEO-3: Solve broad-based problems individually and as a team member communicating effectively in the world of work.<br>\r\n\r\nPEO-4: Pursue higher studies in the field of Power Electronics and allied engineering.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Program specific outcomes (PSOs)</b><br>\r\n\r\nPSO-1: Install and maintain Power Electronics based wind and solar system.<br>\r\n\r\nPSO-2: Use modern tools/softwares related to circuit testing and simulation.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Link for the power electronics department website: </b><br>\r\n\r\nhttps://powssg.wixsite.com/website\" ', '0000-00-00');
INSERT INTO `tb_dept` (`dept_id`, `dept_name`, `dept_desc`, `last_update`) VALUES
(28, 'TEXTILE PROCESSING TECHNOLOGY', ' Surat is a City of Textiles and famous for Synthetic Sarees & Dress Materials. Approximately 450 Textile Processing units are working in Surat. Day by Day Modernization is coming in Textile Industries & therefore to full fill the requirement of technical People are essential. In Dr. S & S.S. Ghandhy College, Textile processing course is running from 1969 by the reorganization of western region committee of technical education and it provides technocrats for Textile Industries. Textile Processing Course is having seven semesters in which six semesters having class room study & practical work and last one semester is Industrial Training.<br><br>\r\n\r\nName of the course   Year of Starting   Duration   Semester/ Annual   Sanctioned student intake\r\nDiploma in Textile Processing Technology  1969  3.5 Years  Semester  60<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>VISION</b><br>\r\n\"To achieve excellence in quality education and to construct technocrats in the areas of textile processing technology to contribute ever-changing need of textile industries and society.\"<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>MISSION </b><br>\r\nTo build up professionally competence students in the field of textile processing.<br>\r\nTo produce technocrats in the field of textile processing technology according to the exact needs of Textile Industries<br>\r\nTo promote creativity, innovation and professional activities in the field of Textile Processing.<br>\r\nTo forge relationship with  reputed institutes, industries and  government bodies  for the benefit of society.<br>\r\nTo provide knowledge through Department-Industry interaction.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Programme Educational Objectives (PEOs)</b><br>\r\nDevelop professional competency for textile processing industries.<br>\r\nUtilize conceptual application of technical skills for textile processing and product development.<br>\r\nAdapt new technologies to serve textile sector.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Programme specific Objectives (PSOs)</b><br>\r\n\r\nExpand technical advancement of textiles in various field for different purposes.<br>\r\nSupport sustainable and ecological development of processing of textiles.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Programme Outcomes (POs)</b><br>\r\nBasic and discipline specific knowledge: “Apply knowledge of basic mathematics, science and engineering fundamentals and engineering specializations to solve the engineering problems”<br>\r\nProblem analysis: “Identify and analyse well defined engineering problems using codified standard methods”<br>\r\nDesign/Development of solutions: “Design solutions for well-defined technical problems and assist with the design of system components or processes to meet specified needs”<br>\r\nEngineering tools, experimentation and Testing: “Apply modern engineering tools and appropriate technique to conduct standard test and measurements”<br>\r\nEngineering practices for society, sustainability and environment: “Apply appropriate technology in context of society, sustainability, environment and ethical practices”<br>\r\nProject management: “Use engineering management principles individually, as a team member or a leader to manage projects and effectively communicate about well-defined engineering activities”<br>\r\nLife-long learning: “Ability to analyse individual needs and engage in updating in the context of the technological changes”<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Training & Placements Opportunities</b><br>\r\n\r\nEvery year students of 7th semester are placed for full term (14 weeks) industrial training as a part of their curriculum in various textile industries of Gujarat region. <br>\r\n\r\nList of industry where students undergone Industrial training in Academic year: 2017   2018   2019<br>\r\n\r\nEach year textile passout students are appointed as processing supervisor in different department by various textile industries. Diploma Processing Graduates are also eligible to apply for DRDO. Approximately 25% of diploma textile graduates are applied for admission in degree engineering program. Diploma graduates can be work as a professional to different textile disciplinaries such as  textile processing houses, research & development laboratories, marketing executive for chemical industries, dyeing & pigment industries and merchandiser for textile & apparel export houses. List of industries/companies hired our graduates in past few years are as mentioned below.<br><br>\r\n\r\n1) Donear Industries Ltd., Surat<br>\r\n2) Welspun India Ltd., Vapi<br>\r\n3) Alok Industries Ltd., Vapi<br>\r\n4) GHCL Ltd., Bhilad<br>\r\n5) Arvind Ltd., Ahmedabad<br>\r\n6) Birla Century, GIDC, Jahgadia<br>\r\n7) DADA Silk Mills, Surat<br>\r\n8) Ginza Industries Ltd., Surat<br>\r\n9) Shivram Processors, Surat<br>\r\n10) Bindal Textiles, Surat<br>\r\n11) Bhavin Textiles (Colourtax), Surat<br>\r\n12) Yash Fashion Pvt. Ltd., Surat<br>\r\n13) Laxmipati Pvt. Ltd., Surat<br>\r\n14) Narayan Processors, Surat<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Co - Curricular and Extracurricular Activities </b><br>\r\n\r\nSeries of Co-curricular and extracurricular activities like Group Discussions, Expert lectures, Industrial visits, Tree plantation, Cleanliness drive, Yoga celebrations, Sports week, NCC and NSS activities are planned and organised in department & institute for a harmonious development of students in respect to their morality, humanity, honesty, character and health. These activities also contribute to the development of soft skills or employable skills to great extent, which are ultimately required at the world of work.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>CONTACT US</b><br>\r\n\r\nDepartment of Textile Processing Technology (DTPT),<br>\r\n\r\nDr. S. & S.S Ghandhy College of Engineering and Technology,<br>\r\n\r\nMajura Gate, Surat-395001<br>\r\n\r\nInstitute E-mail: ssgp-surat-dte@gujarat.gov.in<br>            \r\n\r\nContact No. 0261-2655799<br>\r\n\r\nDepartment E-mail: dtptssg@gmail.com<br>\" ', '0000-00-00'),
(29, 'TEXTILE MANUFACTURING TECHNOLOGY', 'Textile Manufacturing Technology Department established in 1969, is one of the esteemed department of Dr. S. & S. S. Ghandhy College of Engineering And Technology, Surat. Institute is running under Department of Technical Education, Government of Gujarat. Diploma in Textile Manufacturing Technology program is approved by All India council for technical education (AICTE), New Delhi and is affiliated to Gujarat Technological university, Ahmedabad.<br><br>\n\nTextile Manufacturing Technology is a branch of engineering which deals with designing and manufacturing of Apparel Garments and Functional Fabrics. Surat, an emerging city in the state of Gujarat, is known as the textile city of Gujarat. And, the epithet is perfectly suited to the city. The textile industry is one of the oldest and the most widespread industries in Surat. A major part of the city\'s population is associated with the textile industry. Day by Day Textile Industries Upgraded Technically & therefore to full fill the requirement of technical People are essential. The department has qualified faculty members engaged in teaching learning process with the aim of achieving excellence in the field of Textile engineering.<br><br>\n\nSTUDENT INTAKE/YEAR\nName of the course\nYear of Starting\nDuration\nSemester/ Annual\nSanctioned student intake\nDiploma Textile Manufacturing Technology\n1969\n3 Years & 6 Months\nSemester\n30<br><br>\n\n <b>COURSE DURATION</b><br>\n\nDuration of Course is 03 years and 06 months, Seven semesters (including one full term industrial training in 7th semester). Students are undergo Industrial Training in various Textile Industries during 7th SEM as a part of curriculum.<br><br>\n\n<b>ENTRY LEVEL</b><br>\n\n10th Standard Pass (1st Sem. Entry) <br>\nCertificate course of duration 2 years from TEB /NCVT/GCVT/IGTR (3rd Sem. Entry)<br><br>\n\n<b>ADMISSION</b><br>\nAdmission through Central Admission Committee for Professional Diploma Courses on the basis of state level merit List. For More information visit www.acpdc.co.in<br><br>\n\n<b> VISION</b><br>\n\n“Be a Centre of Excellence to prepare students for professional career in Textiles in requirement to the dynamic changes of the industry, society and the Nation.”<br><br>\n\n<b>MISSION</b><br>\n\nTo develop professionally competent textile technocrats.<br>\nTo impart ethical values and leadership qualities to cope up with real world challenges.<br>\nTo provide qualitative education and exposure of textile manufacturing through suitable department-industry interaction.<br>\nUpgrade the student’s performance skills with vocational and industrial training for better placements. <br><br>\n\n<b>PROGRAM EDUCATIONAL OBJECTIVES (PEOs):</b><br>\n\nAnalyse different processes of textile manufacturing industry.<br>\nAcquire expertise to manage the machine and workers shiftwise in different private and public sectors who involves with the manufacturing of fibres, yarns, fabrics and garments.<br>\nSolve real world problems in a safe, professional and ethical manner in order to achieve sustainable growth of industry and society.<br><br>\n\n<b>PROGRAM SPECIFIC OUTCOMES (PSOs):</b><br>\n\nPSO1:- Expand technical advancement of textiles in various field for different Purposes.<br>\nPSO2:- Support sustainable and ecological development of manufacturing of textiles<br><br>\n\n<b>PROGRAM OUTCOMES (POs)</b><br>\n\nBasic and Discipline specific knowledge: Apply knowledge of basic mathematics, science and engineering fundamentals and engineering specialization to solve the engineering problems.<br>\nProblem analysis: Identify and analyse well-defined engineering problems using codified standard methods.<br>\nDesign/ development of solutions: Design solutions for well-defined technical Problems and assist with the design of systems components or processes to meet specified needs.<br>\nEngineering Tools, Experimentation and Testing: Apply modern engineering tools And appropriate technique to conduct standard tests and measurements.<br>\nEngineering practices for society, sustainability and environment: Apply Appropriate technology in context of society, sustainability, environment and ethical practices.<br>\nProject Management: Use engineering management principles individually, as a team member or a leader to manage projects and effectively communicate about well-defined engineering activities.<br>\nLife-long learning: Ability to analyse individual needs and engage in updating in the context of technological changes.<br><br>\n\n<b>TRAINING and PLACEMENTS OPPORTUNITIES:</b><br>\nEvery year students of 7th semester are placed for full term (14 weeks) industrial training as a part of their curriculum in various textile industries of Gujarat region. Each year textile passout students are appointed as processing supervisor in different department by various textile industries. Diploma Processing Graduates are also eligible to apply for DRDO. Approximately 15% of diploma textile graduates are applied for admission in degree engineering program. List of industries/companies hired our graduates in past few years are as mention below.<br>\n\n1) Donear Industries Ltd., Surat<br>\n\n2) Fairdel filaments Ltd. Surat<br>\n\n3) Ginza Industries Ltd., Surat<br>\n\n4) Rajashree polyfils Ltd ,Rajpipla<br>\n\n5) Arvind Mills, Ahmedabad<br>\n\n6) Welspun India Ltd., Vapi<br>\n\n7) Sidhdhi vinayak weavetech pvt.Ltd-surat<br>\n\n8) Mafatlal industries Denim division, Navsari<br>\n\n9) Mayuri Jacquard design, Surat<br>\n\n10) Vardhman Acrylic Ltd, Bharuch<br>\n\n11) Ahlstrom Munksjo Fibrecomposite Pvt. Ltd., Mundra<br>\n\n12) Welspun India Ltd., Mundra, Kutchh.<br>\n\n13) Shri. Dinesh Mills Ltd., Vadodara<br>\n\n14) Garden Silk Mills Ltd., Surat<br><br>\n\n<b>Co-CURRICULAR and EXTRACURRICULAR ACTIVITIES:</b><br>\nSeries of Co-curricular and extracurricular activities like Group Disscussions, Expert lecures, Industrial visits, Tree plantation, Cleanliness drive, Yoga celebrations, Sports week, NCC and NSS activities are planned and organised in & institute for a harmonious development of students in respect to their morality, humanity, honesty, character and health. These activities also contribute to the development of soft skills or employable skills to great extent, which are ultimately required at the world of work.<br><br>\n\n<b>CONTACT US</b><br>\n\nDepartment of Textile manufacturing Technology (DTMT),<br>\n\nDr. S. & S.S Ghandhy College of Engineering and Technology,<br>\n\nMajura Gate, Surat-395001<br>\n\nInstitute E-mail: ssgp-surat-dte@gujarat.gov.in   <br>                             \n\nContact No. 0261-2655799<br>\n\nDepartment E-mail: dtmtssg29@gmail.com<br>\"', '0000-00-00'),
(100, 'GENERAL', '“Science & Humanities Department” is an integral part of every engineering institute which provides knowledge and skills in fundamental subjects like Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, English and CPD to the new entrants of institute.<br><br>\r\n\r\nThe key role of the department is to build strong foundation for diploma entrants by providing them the basic essential Knowledge of Core Science subjects, Problem solving skills and sharpens their Soft and Interpersonal Skills to make them industry ready.<br>\r\n\r\nThe department is well equipped with Physics, Chemistry and English language laboratories and qualified, dynamic and enthusiastic Regular faculties. Department’s main objective is to provide learner-centered environment by innovative and outcome based practices and develop scientific approach and instill life skills to sustain in the industry and to cater the needs of the society.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Vision</b><br>\r\n\r\nTo be a center of excellence in science & humanities in technical education of Gujarat State.<br><br>\r\n\r\n<b>Mission</b><br>\r\n\r\nTo empower diploma students with problem solving skills using analytical, scientific approach and interpersonal skills.<br>\r\nTo sharpen soft and behavioural skills of diploma students.<br>\r\nTo develop analytical and scientific approach for solution of engineering problems.<br>\r\nTo expatiate knowledge and core skills of students in the area of applied science.<br>\r\nThe SHDept created blogs for following courses:<br>\r\nEnglish / CPD : http://www.ssgenglish.blogspot.com<br>\r\nChemistry : http://www.chemistryghandhy.blogspot.com<br>\r\nPhysics : http://www.physicsghandhy.blogspot.com<br>\r\nMathematics : http://www.ghandhymaths.blogspot.com<br>\r\nResult Analysis of subjects offered by the Department: Click Here<br>', '0000-00-00');

